303
00:32:10,150 --> 00:32:13,420
The Gu clan was eminent in the Central Plains.

304
00:32:13,420 --> 00:32:20,820
Your uncle, Gu Ruhui, was a cavalry general of the previous reign. As a young man, he was versed in both literature and military affairs.

305
00:32:20,820 --> 00:32:28,670
He, with your father, together with Chen Zheng and the general of the Sixteenth Prefecture Guards, were close like brothers.

306
00:32:28,670 --> 00:32:33,070
When your father was the crown prince, General Gu and General Chen,

307
00:32:33,070 --> 00:32:38,200
frequently followed your father to fight battles and gained merits.

308
00:32:38,200 --> 00:32:41,560
Your father succeeded to the throne after the former emperor passed away.

309
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:45,000
General Gu was appointed as the Right Minister to command the Three Departments.

310
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:50,990
General Gu was an upright man and won great popularity in Li Empire.

311
00:32:54,730 --> 00:32:59,880
But back then, Left Minister Gao Yuming was full of ambition. He appeared loyal but harbored wickedness.

312
00:32:59,880 --> 00:33:05,240
He didn't get along with General Gu and harbored resentment in his heart.

313
00:33:05,240 --> 00:33:08,890
Minister Gao flattered the emperor and won the emperor's trust.

314
00:33:08,890 --> 00:33:14,930
He secretly established his own power and used every means in his power to eliminate those who opposed him.

315
00:33:14,930 --> 00:33:19,730
He kept making slanderous remarks to the emperor, defaming General Gu for overshadowing the emperor.

316
00:33:19,730 --> 00:33:23,760
He also fabricated letters exchanged between General Gu and Khan Tömür.

317
00:33:23,760 --> 00:33:28,620
He falsely accused General Gu as a traitor colluding with the enemy to start a revolt.

318
00:33:31,170 --> 00:33:37,190
When faced with the evidence present, the emperor started having doubts and ordered Prime Minister Gao to investigate the case.

319
00:33:37,190 --> 00:33:43,690
General Gu and General Chen, whom they thought was related to the case, were brought to the Court of Judicial Review for interrogation.

320
00:33:47,900 --> 00:33:53,720
Prime Minister Gao falsified the royal decree and led the army to charge into the Gu Family Manor for a killing spree.

321
00:33:57,080 --> 00:34:02,330
That night, the blood of the Gu family flowed like a river. Bones piled up into a mountain.

322
00:34:02,330 --> 00:34:07,940
Hundreds of innocent lives died a tragic death under the cold sharp blades.

323
00:34:07,940 --> 00:34:13,930
And dozens of the Chen family members were tragically buried alive.

324
00:34:13,930 --> 00:34:18,870
Even General Chen's wife and daughter couldn't escape.

325
00:34:19,450 --> 00:34:21,700
For a while...

326
00:34:22,860 --> 00:34:25,660
the case of the Gu and Chen families made a great stir in the imperial court.

327
00:34:25,660 --> 00:34:29,520
In front of the emperor, Minister Gao confounded right and wrong.

328
00:34:29,520 --> 00:34:35,630
He brought a false charge against Gu and Chen for collusion and rebellion. They were all executed because they resisted arrest.

329
00:34:35,630 --> 00:34:38,730
His Imperial Majesty was unaware of the truth

330
00:34:38,730 --> 00:34:43,050
and believed Minister Gao's one-sided story. In anger,

331
00:34:43,050 --> 00:34:48,850
the emperor ordered the arrest of General Chen Zheng and the remaining people.

332
00:34:53,730 --> 00:34:57,700
You are... General Chen Zheng?

333
00:35:04,050 --> 00:35:06,260
Yes, I am.

334
00:35:06,260 --> 00:35:09,530
General Chen, please rise.

335
00:35:12,230 --> 00:35:16,040
You have suffered... all these years.

336
00:35:16,040 --> 00:35:19,110
General Gu and I went on expeditions for so many years.

337
00:35:19,110 --> 00:35:23,540
I am indebted to him for saving my life. I'm still alive because of him.

338
00:35:23,540 --> 00:35:28,940
But Fifth Prince, please remember this... Chen Zheng is dead.

339
00:35:28,940 --> 00:35:34,210
My name is Chai Mu.

340
00:35:36,920 --> 00:35:38,600
Right.

341
00:35:38,600 --> 00:35:41,080
Aunt, what happened afterward?

342
00:35:41,080 --> 00:35:46,040
Afterward, Minister Gao took your uncle's position.

343
00:35:46,040 --> 00:35:50,460
For a while, it was magnificent.

344
00:35:50,460 --> 00:35:55,810
Secretly, he instigated other ministers to implore the emperor to abolish Consort Shu and banish her to the cold palace.

345
00:35:55,810 --> 00:36:01,340
The emperor was deeply in love with your mother and reluctant to give the order.

346
00:36:03,710 --> 00:36:08,590
In the palace, your mother was devastated over the news of the extermination of the Gu family.

347
00:36:08,590 --> 00:36:15,470
In order not to make things difficult for the emperor, she asked to be demoted as a commoner and to live outside the palace to cultivate in seclusion.

348
00:36:15,470 --> 00:36:20,810
His Imperial Majesty had no choice but to order people to build another Jade Collecting Hall outside the capital.

349
00:36:20,810 --> 00:36:25,000
